overview: The user requested a thorough review of their sleep questionnaire
  application to ensure it met all specified acceptance criteria. The agent
  performed a detailed analysis of the existing codebase against the provided
  functional and content requirements. This review highlighted several critical
  gaps, including the absence of a tiredness severity scale with safety
  warnings, lack of detection for specific sleep disorders like COMISA and
  Insufficient Sleep Syndrome, missing outbound links in the generated reports,
  and incomplete data in the CSV export. The agent then proceeded to implement
  these identified features, updating the application's data types, validation
  schemas, user interface components, and report generation logic. This included
  adding new questions for pain and chronic fatigue screening, enhancing the
  diagnostic capabilities of the report, and improving data accessibility for
  administrators.
